==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Orgue
<hw>Orgue</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. L.
<ets>organum</ets> organ, Gr. <?/. See <er>Organ</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Mil.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Any one of a number of long, thick
pieces of timber, pointed and shod with iron, and suspended, each by a
separate rope, over a gateway, to be let down in case of attack.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>A piece of ordnance, consisting of a number of musket
barrels arranged so that a match or train may connect with all their
touchholes, and a discharge be secured almost or quite
simultaneously.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Orgulous</ent>⟦br⟧
